--------------
 Translations
--------------

This project uses Launchpad for translations. In Launchpad you can find
translations for more languages.

The translations that exist in this directory is obtained from launchpad,
for details of translators visit: https://translations.launchpad.net/pysum

Translations submitted in Launchpad licensed using the simplified BSD licence,
see: https://help.launchpad.net/Translations/LicensingFAQ

This project and its developers are not responsible for the content of the
translations


----------------------
 Install Translations
----------------------

The program use the default directory for translations (usually 
/usr/share/locale/ on a GNU/Linux, but on Solaris it is /usr/lib/locale)

You can translate the *.pot or *.po file (using poEdit, KBabel, gtranslator or
launchpad) and next generate a *.mo file. You should copy the *.mo file into
your locate directory (on GNU/Linux: localedir/language/LC_MESSAGES/pysum.mo).
For example, if you use a translation into Spanish, copy the *.mo file to:
/usr/share/locale/es/LC_MESSAGES/pysum.mo 


----------------
 help translate
----------------

If you want to help translate pySum, please visit:
https://translations.launchpad.net/pysum

Login with your account (or sign-up) and begins to translate. Permits for the
project are set Open (anyone can submit translations)

If you have any questions, please read
https://help.launchpad.net/Translations/StartingToTranslate
